## Decisions Made
- Extract batch-branch guard into a shared helper rather than duplicating inline checks: reduces maintenance burden and ensures consistency across all four vault-write functions
- Use `git symbolic-ref --short HEAD` instead of `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD`: symbolic-ref correctly returns the branch name on unborn branches (no commits), where rev-parse returns literal "HEAD"
- Guard `add_entry()` (the `add` CLI command) in addition to pipeline commands: this was the most likely bypass vector since it's a public API with no prior guard

## Problems Encountered
- `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD` returns literal "HEAD" (not an error) on unborn branches, so the `||` fallback never triggered: resolved by switching to `git symbolic-ref --short HEAD`
- Test repo had no commits so `git checkout main` failed after testing on batch branch: resolved by creating an initial commit before branching and using `git checkout -` to return

## Constraints Identified
- The `_KD_VIA_CHANGESET_APPLY` env var bypass must remain for `changeset_apply()` to work on batch branches post-merge: the guard checks this first and returns early

