## Context
Investigated intermittent direct vault.db writes during batch-refine pipeline execution. Found that only `pipeline_insert()` had the batch-branch guard while `add_entry()`, `pipeline_archive()`, and `pipeline_update()` were unguarded. Extracted a shared `assert_not_batch_branch()` helper, applied it to all four functions, and added comprehensive tests. The existing `changeset_apply()` idempotency (skip by ID) already handles duplicates correctly.

